{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3e2ba29d-83d0-418e-a064-19cb3d1048f5","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove or keep (still works as fallback): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Update adapter: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"5.0.0\" />\n\n   <!-- Add: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.NUnit\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- **NUnit3TestAdapter 5.0+** is required — it adds the Microsoft.Testing.Platform server mode.\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.NUnit` bridges NUnit to the new platform.\n- You can remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` once fully migrated, but keeping it allows fallback to VSTest.\n- Your test code (`[Test]`, `[TestFixture]`, assertions, etc.) requires **no changes**.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a5b8363-9751-4bb6-80e1-0a3225fea9b8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I don't need to search a codebase for this. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":397,"requestId":"9827:1C6BCC:1904A3:2001CE:69FFD7DC"},"id":"3cd39905-ed47-47bb-b674-feef30b50010","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:57:09.888Z","parentId":"1cbda823-5955-48b3-90d6-7d9d99ef8e96"}
